'''Joel M. Toledo''' (born 1972) is a poet, fictionist, critic, and journalist based in [[Quezon City]], Metro Manila, [[Philippines]]. He has been granted residencies by the [[Rockefeller Foundation]]<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|title=Fault Setting poems {{!}} University of the Philippines Press|url=https://press.up.edu.ph/project/fault-setting-poems-2/|access-date=2021-03-24|language=en-US}}</ref> in Bellagio, Italy, and the International Writing Program (IWP)<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|title=TOLEDO, Joel {{!}} The International Writing Program|url=https://iwp.uiowa.edu/writers/joel-toledo|url-status=live}}</ref> in Iowa, United States. 

== Early life and education ==

He grew up in the town of [[Silang, Cavite]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=2011-07-15|title=Chiaroscuro: a meeting with Filipino poet Joel M Toledo|url=https://www.abc.net.au/radionational/programs/archived/poetica/chiaroscuro-a-meeting-with-filipino-poet-joel-m/2924322|access-date=2021-03-27|website=Radio National|language=en-AU}}</ref> He holds a masterâ€™s degree in poetry from the [[University of the Philippines]] in Diliman, where he also finished two undergraduate degrees ([[creative writing]] and [[journalism]]).<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|date=2011-07-15|title=Chiaroscuro: a meeting with Filipino poet Joel M Toledo|url=https://www.abc.net.au/radionational/programs/archived/poetica/chiaroscuro-a-meeting-with-filipino-poet-joel-m/2924322|access-date=2021-03-27|website=Radio National|language=en-AU}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2018-05-24|title=Toledo, Joel M.|url=http://panitikan.ph/2018/05/25/joel-m-toledo/|access-date=2021-03-27|website=panitikan.ph|language=en-US}}</ref>

